Package edu.rpi.legup.model.tree

Class TreeElement

java.lang.Object
edu.rpi.legup.model.tree.TreeElement
Direct Known Subclasses:
TreeNode, TreeTransition
public abstract class TreeElement extends Object
Represents an element in a tree structure, which can be either a TreeNode or a TreeTransition.

    • isContradictoryBranch

      public abstract boolean isContradictoryBranch()
      Determines if this tree node leads to a contradiction. Every path from this tree node must lead to a contradiction including all of its children
      Returns:
      true if this tree node leads to a contradiction, false otherwise

    • isValidBranch

      public abstract boolean isValidBranch()
      Recursively determines if the subtree rooted at this tree puzzleElement is valid by checking whether this tree puzzleElement and all descendants of this tree puzzleElement is justified and justified correctly
      Returns:
      true if this tree puzzleElement and all descendants of this tree puzzleElement is valid, false otherwise
